===Etymology 1===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*(s)pend-}}
From {{inh|en|enm|pound}}, from {{inh|en|ang|pund||a pound, weight}}, from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*pund}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*pundą||pound, weight}}, an early borrowing from {{der|en|la|pondō||by weight}}, ablative form of {{m|la|pondus||weight}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*(s)pend-||to pull, stretch}}. 

Cognate with {{cog|nl|pond}}, {{cog|de|Pfund}}, {{cog|da|pund}} and {{cog|sv|pund}}. {{doublet|en|funt|pfund|pood|punt<id:Irish pound>}}.

